{"body": ["<tr><th>Project/Area Number</th><td>20340049</td></tr>", "<tr>\n     <th>Research Category</th>\n     <td>\n      \n    <p> \n        \n        \n      <a href=\"/search/?qc=Grant-in-Aid%20for%20Scientific%20Research%20%28B%29\" class=\"link-page underline\">Grant-in-Aid for Scientific Research (B)</a>\n    \n    </p>\n     </td></tr>", "<tr><th>Allocation Type</th><td>Single-year Grants</td></tr>", "<tr><th>Section</th><td>\u4e00\u822c</td></tr>", "<tr><th>Research Field</th>\n      <td>\n      \n      <a href=\"/search/?qd=Science%20and%20Engineering/Mathematics%20and%20Physics/Physics/Particle/Nuclear/Cosmic%20ray/Astro%20physics\" class=\"link-page underline\">Particle/Nuclear/Cosmic ray/Astro physics</a>\n      \n        </td></tr>", "<tr><th>Research Institution</th><td><a href=\"/search/?qe=The%20University%20of%20Tokyo\" class=\"link-page underline\">The University of Tokyo</a></td></tr>", "<tr><th><h3><strong>Principal Investigator</strong></h3></th>\n          <td>\n          <h4><span><a href=\"/search/?qm=60282505\">ASAI Shoji</a></span>\u00a0\u00a0The University of Tokyo,\u00a0\u5927\u5b66\u9662\u30fb\u7406\u5b66\u7cfb\u7814\u7a76\u79d1,\u00a0\u51c6\u6559\u6388\u00a0(60282505)</h4>\n          </td></tr>", "<tr><th><strong>Co-Investigator(Kenky\u016b-buntansha)</strong></th>\n          <td>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=80020197\">\u51fa\u539f \u654f\u5b5d</a>\u00a0\u00a0\u798f\u4e95\u5927\u5b66,\u00a0\u9060\u8d64\u5916\u9818\u57df\u958b\u767a\u7814\u7a76\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc,\u00a0\u7279\u4efb\u6559\u6388\u00a0(80020197)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=60235059\">\u9f4b\u85e4 \u6674\u96c4</a>\u00a0\u00a0\u6771\u4eac\u5927\u5b66,\u00a0\u5927\u5b66\u9662\u30fb\u7dcf\u5408\u6587\u5316\u7814\u7a76\u79d1,\u00a0\u51c6\u6559\u6388\u00a0(60235059)\n          </td></tr>", "<tr><th><strong>Co-Investigator(Renkei-kenky\u016bsha)</strong></th>\n          <td>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=50126059\">KOBAYASHI Tomio</a>\u00a0\u00a0\u6771\u4eac\u5927\u5b66,\u00a0\u7d20\u7c92\u5b50\u7269\u7406\u56fd\u969b\u7814\u7a76\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc,\u00a0\u6559\u6388\u00a0(50126059)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=40376702\">NAMBA Toshio</a>\u00a0\u00a0\u6771\u4eac\u5927\u5b66,\u00a0\u7d20\u7c92\u5b50\u7269\u7406\u56fd\u969b\u7814\u7a76\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc,\u00a0\u52a9\u6559\u00a0(40376702)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=60235059\">SAITO Haruo</a>\u00a0\u00a0\u6771\u4eac\u5927\u5b66,\u00a0\u7dcf\u5408\u6587\u5316\u7814\u7a76\u79d1,\u00a0\u51c6\u6559\u6388\u00a0(60235059)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=80020197\">IDEHARA Toshitaka</a>\u00a0\u00a0\u798f\u4e95\u5927\u5b66,\u00a0\u9060\u8d64\u5916\u9818\u57df\u958b\u767a\u7814\u7a76\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc,\u00a0\u7279\u4efb\u6559\u6388\u00a0(80020197)\n          </td></tr>", "<tr>\n     <th>Project Period (FY)</th>\n     <td>\n      <span class=\"fiscal_year\">2008\u00a0\u2013\u00a02010</span>\n     </td>\n    </tr>", "<tr>\n     <th>Project Status</th>\n     <td>\n      <span class=\"pstatus\">Completed(Fiscal Year 2010)</span>\n     </td>\n    </tr>", "<tr><th>Budget Amount\u00a0<a class=\"award_amount_help\" href=\"https://support.nii.ac.jp/kaken/project_details\" onclick=\"return winOpen(this.href);\">*help</a></th>\n    <td>\n     <h5>\u00a519,500,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a515,000,000\u3001Indirect Cost : \u00a54,500,000)</h5>\n     \n     Fiscal Year 2010 : \u00a51,300,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a51,000,000\u3001Indirect Cost : \u00a5300,000)<br>\n     \n     Fiscal Year 2009 : \u00a55,070,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a53,900,000\u3001Indirect Cost : \u00a51,170,000)<br>\n     \n     Fiscal Year 2008 : \u00a513,130,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a510,100,000\u3001Indirect Cost : \u00a53,030,000)\n     \n    </td></tr>", "<tr><th>Keywords</th><td>\u30dd\u30b8\u30c8\u30ed\u30cb\u30a6\u30e0 / \u91cf\u5b50\u96fb\u78c1\u6c17\u5b66 / \u30c6\u30e9\u30d8\u30eb\u30c4\u6ce2 / \u8d85\u5fae\u7d30\u69cb\u9020 / \u30b8\u30e3\u30a4\u30ed\u30c8\u30ed\u30f3</td></tr>", "<tr>\n      <th>Research Abstract</th>\n      <td>\n        <p>Positronium is an ideal system for the research of the bound state QED. The hyperfine splitting of positronium (Ps-HFS, about 203 GHz) is an important observable but all previous measurement Ps-HFS employed static magnetic field and measured Ps-HFS indirectly using Zeeman splitting. We propose new method to measure Ps-HFS directly using sub-THz radiation. We developed an optical system to accumulate high power (about 10 kW) radiation in a Fabry-Perot resonant cavity and observed the positronium hyperfine transition for the first time.\n        \n        </p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>"]}
